    value: The 'Great Progenitor' (High Progenitor/Liu Bang) was the founder of the Han Dynasty. The incident with the 'bowl of broth' (杯羹) refers to his response when confronted by his enemy Xiang Yu during their struggle for supremacy.
  - key: ''
    value: Wu Qi (吳起) was a renowned general and strategist of the Warring States period, notorious in Confucian tradition for his disregard of family bonds in pursuit of advancement—he reputedly killed his own wife to demonstrate his willingness to severe personal ties.
  - key: ''
    value: Wang Ling's mother, facing capture, chose suicide to prevent her son from being coerced into betraying his sovereign, setting a model of maternal virtue that prioritized loyalty above family preservation.
  - key: ''
    value: Zhao Bao (趙苞) was a Han Dynasty official. The historical record shows he was indeed commended by many for his choice, though this essay argues his understanding of true loyalty and filial piety remained incomplete.
